  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Andrew Paton encloses an invoice for a box of contributions sent by the Glasgow Female Anti-Slavery Society to the Boston annual anti-slavery bazaar. The box also includes contributions from London and Preston, and parcels for H. C. Wright, Wendell Phillips, and a book for Samuel May.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On pages 1-2 of this letter, there is a list of &quot;Contributions sent from the Glasgow Female Anti Slavery Society to the Boston Bazaar, 1857,&quot; with prices.</subfield>
  </datafield>
